{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The windows explorer is not a {\f1 simple} piece of software built by Microsoft. It is rather a quite complicated system that includes the tools and exposes the interfaces required so as to make development and integration a not that hard of a process. All that is required is access to documentation and code samples that /lead the way/. With that knowledge at hand the explorer is as customizable as it could be - to some extent - of course.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The {\f1 IFilterShellView} is an extension built for the windows explorer that improves the searching experience and allows a broad spectrum of actions to be performed on the filtered folders and files. The following methods of filtering items are suported at the time: * Via text placement (e.g in the beggining or ending or in the middle of the text) * Via regular expresion * Via parsed command that supports filtering via attributes (e.g dates, size, type, extension, ...) as well as the above\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The methods can be extended and will be in the future with your support and feedback. The plugin extends the normal behaviour of the windows explorer and minimizes the time you would usually spend searching for items. Moreover it is built using controls that feel native to the windows ecosistem and integrate with the current installed theme. It is a theme aware project which means you don't have to worry for a bright light during the night.\par}
