{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Installing the binaries\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To install the latest version of the plugin {\f1 IFilterShellView} you have to download the latest binaries from the release page and install them. You can choose to either download the installer or download the portable version.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Getting Started\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 After the intallation is complete, run the recently installed image named distinctively {\f1 IFilterShellView.exe}. It can be found inside the installation folder (either the default one or the one set by you during the installation).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To {\f1 /summon/} the instance of {\f1 IFilterShellView} * Bring forward a new explorer window and navigate to a folder populated with items. * Press the hotkey {\f1 CTRL+F}. A nice window should popup on top of the explorer window.\par}
