{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Warning\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 IFilterShellView} can only filter through items that have a physical corespondent on the disk. In other words you cannot filter through elements of a virtual folder inside the namespace such as {\f1 My Computer} or {\f1 This PC} or {\f1 Control Panel} etc.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 How to use\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 With the {\f1 IFilterShellView} filter window now open, start typing a search query inside the text input and results with matched data will start showing up. As an item is matched against your search query, it is automatically selected inside the explorer window. That means that after the searching is done you can move/copy/rename all the selected items from the explorer window.\par}
